---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Projects | My Portfolio" lang="en">
  <section>
    <h2>Engineering Projects</h2>

    <article>
      <h3>Wichat — Quiz Web App</h3>
      <p class="date">Software Architecture | 2025</p>
      <p>
        Web application inspired by the TV show "Saber y Ganar". It implements a
        robust architecture based on the <strong>Gateway Pattern</strong> to centralize
        communication between microservices. Includes the integration of an <strong
          >LLM Chatbot</strong
        > to enhance user experience. The project was developed following Agile methodologies.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/Arquisoft/wichat_en2a"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">View repository</a
        >
      </p>
      <p class="stack-list">
        <strong>Stack:</strong> React, Node.js, Gateway Pattern, LLM, MongoDB.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article>
      <h3>RecadOS — Android App</h3>
      <p class="date">Mobile Software Development | 2025</p>
      <p>
        Native application for collaborative errand and task management.
        Developed in <strong>Kotlin</strong>, it leverages the <strong
          >Google Cloud Firebase</strong
        > ecosystem for real-time data persistence and user authentication. The project
        was carried out following the SCRUM framework.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/SergioMulet/RecadOS"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">View repository</a
        >
      </p>
      <p class="stack-list">
        <strong>Stack:</strong> Kotlin, Android SDK, Firebase.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article>
      <h3>Information Retrieval Systems</h3>
      <p class="date">Information repositories | 2024</p>
      <p>
        Development of an advanced search engine comparing lexical (<strong
          >BM25</strong
        >) and semantic (<strong>Vector Embeddings</strong>) retrieval methods.
        The project focuses on result optimization through query expansion and <strong
          >Reranking</strong
        > techniques, evaluating system performance using precision and F1-Score metrics
        on the NFCorpus dataset.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/SergioMulet/Information_retrieval"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">View repository</a
        >
      </p>
      <p class="stack-list">
        <strong>Stack:</strong> Python, BM25s, ChromaDB, Sentence-Transformers, PyTorch.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article>
      <h3>Corporate Network Simulation</h3>
      <p class="date">Systems and Network Administration | 2025</p>
      <p>
        Design and deployment of an internal network infrastructure using <strong
          >Docker Compose</strong
        >. The project orchestrates a complete business environment including a
        DNS server (BIND9) for internal name resolution, an Nginx web server, a
        MySQL database, and custom clients, validating connectivity and data
        flow in an isolated and controlled environment.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/SergioMulet/Red-Docker"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">View repository</a
        >
      </p>
      <p class="stack-list">
        <strong>Stack:</strong> Docker, Docker Compose, BIND9 (DNS), Nginx, MySQL.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
